{"questionId":"22158689","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Roma decides to test the model. They charge the phone from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo> </mo><mo>%</mo></math> and record the charge of the phone for different values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>. The results are shown in the following table.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/c6cd4c7527e73a03c4540742129ceb9d2727b454.png\" width=\"542\" height=\"66\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>the quadratic model.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>The sum of the square residuals is smaller so it is a better fit&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22158689","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ1.12ci","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"the quadratic model.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
